  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/standards/ANTI-PATTERNS.md — top 20 anti-patterns sourced from deploy skills, ADRs, and incident history</goal>
    <context>Anti-patterns are scattered across deploy skill troubleshooting tables, ADR DON'T rules, and CLAUDE.md warnings. Claude repeatedly hits the same pitfalls because there is no consolidated anti-pattern reference. This document provides a single lookup for "what NOT to do" with explanations and correct alternatives.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-standards skill structure
      - Source ALL anti-patterns from existing deploy skills, ADRs, and CLAUDE.md — do not invent
      - Format each entry as: Anti-Pattern → Why It's Wrong → Correct Approach → Source Reference
      - Target exactly 20 anti-patterns covering deployment, coding, architecture, and security concerns
      - Prioritize anti-patterns that cause production incidents or repeated CI failures
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/docs-standards/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/bff-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/pcf-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/code-page-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/azure-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api-and-workers.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-002-thin-dataverse-plugins.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006-anti-legacy-js.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spe-filestore-facade.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters-for-auth.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-009-redis-first-caching.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-ui-v9.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-pcf-platform-libraries.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read .claude/skills/docs-standards/SKILL.md for mandatory structure</step>
    <step>Read all deploy skills (bff-deploy, pcf-deploy, code-page-deploy, dataverse-deploy, azure-deploy) and extract troubleshooting tables and warnings</step>
    <step>Read all ADRs and extract every DON'T rule and negative constraint</step>
    <step>Read CLAUDE.md and extract all "DON'T" and "WRONG" examples</step>
    <step>Rank anti-patterns by severity and frequency, select top 20</step>
    <step>Draft ANTI-PATTERNS.md with consistent format: Anti-Pattern → Why Wrong → Correct Approach → Source</step>
    <step>Verify every anti-pattern cites its source document</step>
    <step>Write to docs/standards/ANTI-PATTERNS.md</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Grep</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Skill(docs-standards)</tool>
  </tools>
  <outputs>
    <output>docs/standards/ANTI-PATTERNS.md</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
